*********Method Overriding (Interview Notes)

1. What is Method Overriding?
Definition
Method Overriding occurs when a child class provides its own implementation of a method that already exists in the parent class.

Interview Definition
Method Overriding is the process in which a child class redefines a parent class method with the same method name, same parameter list, and compatible return type.

2. Why Do We Need Method Overriding?
Suppose every animal has a sound() method.
Without overriding
class Animal {

    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Animal Sound");
    }
}

Now create Dog.

class Dog extends Animal {

}
Dog d = new Dog();
d.sound();
Output
Animal Sound

Question:
Does a dog make an "Animal Sound"?
❌ No.
Every animal has a different sound.
We need Dog to provide its own implementation.

Solution
class Animal {

    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Animal Sound");
    }
}

class Dog extends Animal {

    @Override
    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Bark");
    }
}
Dog d = new Dog();
d.sound();
Output
Bark
Now Dog behaves like a Dog.

2------------  Rules of Method Overriding

For overriding, the child method must have:

