Q2 What is a VTable?

A table storing addresses of virtual functions.

Q3 What is VPTR?

A hidden pointer inside objects that points to the VTable.

Q4 Why do we need Virtual Inheritance?

To solve the Diamond Problem by ensuring only one shared copy of the common base class.

Q5 Does Java have VTable?

The JVM uses internal dispatch tables to implement dynamic method dispatch, but the exact implementation is JVM-dependent. Unlike C++, Java programmers do not work directly with a concept called a VTable.

