Q. What is the difference between virtual and virtual inheritance?

Answer:

virtual function is used to achieve runtime polymorphism. It lets C++ choose the correct overridden method at runtime using a VTable and VPTR.
Virtual inheritance is used in multiple inheritance to solve the Diamond Problem by ensuring there is only one shared copy of the common base class. 
They solve completely different problems.
